{
  "stem": "15943.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Jewish police only come-- came to look if there's-- of those people who were on a list for deportation.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was never on a list for deportation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they didn't come to look for him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we really didn't have to hide him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We only hid him that time when we went out, when they surrounded the ghetto, when my mother was taken away.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So just the time that he was really hidden, in that-- in that root cellar.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Otherwise, we-- we didn't hide him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1943, April 23rd.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He just died, couldn't go on any longer.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mm-hmm.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[DRINKS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] When she stood outside, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] [SOBBING] she showed her papers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 11 SECONDS] And she said, I am a good worker.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the-- [INAUDIBLE] [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] [SOBBING] the guard said, no, you are a sick old woman.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And they-- they pulled her-- [SOBS] I'm sorry.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[DRINKS] They pulled her on a wagon, and the Jewish police held her back.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And they sped off.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SOBBING] Right next to her.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 10 SECONDS] I was at the line, you know, for the selections.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And Motele and Moishele and I, we were sent back to the ones that remained in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The ones for deportation were put in the wagon.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] The [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] welfare department of the ghetto had found out that we're four children without supervision.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they-- there were a lot of people that their children were taken away.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they felt that they could divide us, and the people that lost their children would take us in.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[SIGHS] But they wanted to take Laibele and put him in an orphanage.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
